  Anthony Martial and Harry Maguire scored to give Manchester United a 2-0 victory over Chelsea at Stamford Bridge in the English Premier League. Martial headed in a beautiful cross at the stroke of halftime to give the Red Devils the lead and Harry Maguire made it 2-0 with another header converted The Video Assistant Referee ruled out goals that would have changed the scoreline. Odion Ighalo also made his debut, coming in for Anthony Martial in the 90th minute. This victory further boosts Manchester United’s chances of playing in the UEFA Champions League next season.  Details Shortly……….